<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-03T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-03T19:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.20/38: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Minister in Honduras</hi>
                                        (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-03T19:00:00-05:00">December 3, 1940—7 p.m.</date></dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>52. Your telegram no. 76, November 18, noon. War Department
                                    states the Commanding General, Panama Canal Department,<note n="85" xml:id="d169fn1">Gen. Daniel Van Voorhis.</note> has
                                    sent Colonel Serafin M. Montesinos to Tegucigalpa to make a
                                    survey of the requirements of the Honduran Government and to
                                    submit a report to the War Department.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>